HEADWORD: insidiousness
<hw>insidiousness</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A subtle and cumulative
harmfulness, especially of a disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the quality of being designed to entrap.</def>⟦br⟧
